{"parentUuid":"8bb5cfe9-438d-423d-8299-73af08bb39d6","isSidechain":false,"promptId":"50b29109-9f82-4292-90db-ca78467a1857","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":"1. The tool list should come from our dotfiles repo, thats where this is all going to live. If i get another machine, im gonig to download the dotfiles, to install programs, add config files, and backup data etc. Dotfiles repo is the core of how i work on machines. So we should maybe have ~/.dotifles/installer etc. \n\n2. yeah, i think we mentioned this in the .md file, modular checking system, so it iterates over predefined modules, and generates an object stored list with instructinos on how to store. So apt, should save a list of apt based programs, and when installer->install(apt) runs, it grabs the apt programs. This way we can easily add in flatpak whent he day comes around that we fancy using that. Also in order to add a program to the list, all we need todo is all a program to a specific list. E.g. add jagex launcher to the flatpak list. then run install.sh and it will grab it from the list."},"uuid":"4253f58d-c01b-4d05-af04-8991a801039a","timestamp":"2026-04-01T08:37:35.314Z","permissionMode":"default","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/home/sudo-haggis/workshop/backup_scripts","sessionId":"dd1e1896-dd31-4a3f-bd5e-5575827249af","version":"2.1.89","gitBranch":"HEAD"}
