{"parentUuid":"45163ba2-e2c7-46bc-b381-8fc47d27aa1c","isSidechain":false,"message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_019XWTP8VfLckk3vxuTk5Lv5","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Makes sense — keep it all consistent plain text. Here's what I'd suggest:\n\n**`apt.txt` / `snap.txt` / `flatpak.txt`** — package manager handles versioning via `=`:\n```\nbat\nripgrep\ntmux=3.3a\ngit\nstow\n```\n\n**`manual.txt`** — pipe-delimited, single line per tool:\n```\n# name|check_cmd|install_cmd\nclaude-code|claude|npm install -g @anthropic-ai/claude-code@latest\nnvm|nvm|curl -o- https://raw.githubusercontent.com/nvm-sh/nvm/v0.40.3/install.sh | bash\n```\n\n`check_cmd` is just the binary name to test with `command -v`. The version lives in the install command itself where it matters.\n\nComments (`#`) ignored by the parser in all files.\n\n---\n\nThis means the full `programs/` directory is:\n\n```\nprograms/\n├── apt.txt\n├── snap.txt\n├── flatpak.txt\n└── manual.txt\n```\n\nAll human-readable, trivially diff-able across branches, no parser dependencies beyond basic bash string splitting.\n\nHappy with that? Then we can start building — I'd suggest starting with the program files themselves and the `apt` module as the first working piece."}],"stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1342,"cache_read_input_tokens":19699,"output_tokens":880,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1342,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"requestId":"req_011CZckdiN6uqJ98Nw2KrDB6","type":"assistant","uuid":"b13cf0e0-b7df-414b-badb-bde859e1c768","timestamp":"2026-04-01T08:41:56.070Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/home/sudo-haggis/workshop/backup_scripts","sessionId":"dd1e1896-dd31-4a3f-bd5e-5575827249af","version":"2.1